---
import RedSectionHeader from "../common/RedSectionHeader.astro";
---

<section class="py-20 bg-gray-50" id="life-stages">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <RedSectionHeader
            title="Strategy by Life Stage: One Size Does Not Fit All"
            className="mb-12"
        />

        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-700 max-w-none">
            <p class="mb-12">
                Your 3rd pillar strategy at age 25 should look completely
                different from your strategy at age 55. We've broken down the
                optimal approach for the four critical phases of an expat's
                financial life.
            </p>

            <!-- 7.1 Young Professionals (25-35) -->
            <div
                class="mb-16 bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border-l-8 border-green-500"
            >
                <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
                    <div class="bg-green-100 p-3 rounded-full">
                        <!-- Icon Placeholder -->
                        <svg
                            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                            class="h-6 w-6 text-green-600"
                            fill="none"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                        >
                            <path
                                stroke-linecap="round"
                                stroke-linejoin="round"
                                stroke-width="2"
                                d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6"></path>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 m-0">
                        The Builder (Age 25-35)
                    </h3>
                </div>
                <p
                    class="text-sm font-bold text-green-700 mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide"
                >
                    Goal: Maximum Aggression & compounding
                </p>

                <p class="mb-4">
                    You have ~35 years until retirement. Volatility is your
                    friend. A market crash today is irrelevant to the "You" of
                    2060.
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mb-6 text-sm">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Strategy:</strong> 97-99% Equity (Stocks). Do not
                        hold cash or bonds in your 3rd pillar.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Provider:</strong> Low-cost digital bank (Finpension,
                        VIAC).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Contribution:</strong> Try to hit the max (CHF 7,258),
                        but even CHF 200/month starts the clock.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Tax Hack:</strong> Reinvest your tax refund from the
                        3a deduction into a taxable ETF portfolio (3b).
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded text-sm italic">
                    "<strong>Math Proof:</strong> CHF 7,000 invested at age 25 @ 7%
                    return becomes ~CHF 105,000 by age 65. The same CHF 7,000 invested
                    at age 55 becomes only ~CHF 13,000. Start now."
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 7.2 Families (35-50) -->
            <div
                class="mb-16 bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border-l-8 border-blue-500"
            >
                <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
                    <div class="bg-blue-100 p-3 rounded-full">
                        <svg
                            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                            class="h-6 w-6 text-blue-600"
                            fill="none"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                        >
                            <path
                                stroke-linecap="round"
                                stroke-linejoin="round"
                                stroke-width="2"
                                d="M3 12l2-2m0 0l7-7 7 7M5 10v10a1 1 0 001 1h3m10-11l2 2m-2-2v10a1 1 0 01-1 1h-3m-6 0a1 1 0 001-1v-4a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v4a1 1 0 001 1m-6 0h6"
                            ></path>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 m-0">
                        The Protector (Age 35-50)
                    </h3>
                </div>
                <p
                    class="text-sm font-bold text-blue-700 mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide"
                >
                    Goal: Security, Home Ownership & Tax Efficiency
                </p>

                <p class="mb-4">
                    Peak earnings often collide with peak costs (kids,
                    mortgage). The 3rd pillar becomes a multi-tool.
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mb-6 text-sm">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Strategy:</strong> Still high equity (60-80%), but
                        verify risk tolerance.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Home Ownership:</strong> You can pledge (verpf√§nden)
                        your 3a account to banks for a mortgage down payment. This
                        keeps the money invested and growing while securing your home
                        loan.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Spousal Logic:</strong> Ensure both partners have
                        accounts to break progressive withdrawal taxes later.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Risk:</strong> Consider a Term Life Insurance policy
                        outside the 3a to protect the mortgage.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- 7.3 Pre-Retirement (50-65) -->
            <div
                class="mb-16 bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border-l-8 border-orange-500"
            >
                <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
                    <div class="bg-orange-100 p-3 rounded-full">
                        <svg
                            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                            class="h-6 w-6 text-orange-600"
                            fill="none"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                        >
                            <path
                                stroke-linecap="round"
                                stroke-linejoin="round"
                                stroke-width="2"
                                d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"
                            ></path>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 m-0">
                        The Strategist (Age 50-65)
                    </h3>
                </div>
                <p
                    class="text-sm font-bold text-orange-700 mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide"
                >
                    Goal: Preservation & Exit Planning
                </p>

                <p class="mb-4">
                    You are in the "Red Zone." Focus shifts from aggressive
                    growth to capital preservation and tax-efficient exit.
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mb-6 text-sm">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Strategy:</strong> Glide path down to 20-40% equity.
                        Protect what you've built.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>The "Staggering" Rule:</strong> Open multiple 3a accounts
                        (up to 5). You cannot make partial withdrawals from one account.
                        By having 5 accounts, you can close one at age 60, one at
                        61, 62, etc., breaking the progressive tax rate on lump sums.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Buy-Ins:</strong> Consider diverting cash to 2nd Pillar
                        buy-ins for even larger tax deductions if your 3a is maxed.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- 7.4 Self-Employed -->
            <div
                class="mb-16 bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border-l-8 border-purple-500"
            >
                <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
                    <div class="bg-purple-100 p-3 rounded-full">
                        <svg
                            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                            class="h-6 w-6 text-purple-600"
                            fill="none"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                        >
                            <path
                                stroke-linecap="round"
                                stroke-linejoin="round"
                                stroke-width="2"
                                d="M21 13.255A23.931 23.931 0 0112 15c-3.183 0-6.22-.62-9-1.745M16 6V4a2 2 0 00-2-2h-4a2 2 0 00-2 2v2m4 6h.01M5 20h14a2 2 0 002-2V8a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"
                            ></path>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 m-0">
                        The Entrepreneur (Self-Employed)
                    </h3>
                </div>
                <p
                    class="text-sm font-bold text-purple-700 mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide"
                >
                    Goal: Replacing the 2nd Pillar
                </p>

                <p class="mb-4">
                    Without an employer pension, the 3rd pillar is your
                    lifeline. It is likely your primary retirement vehicle.
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mb-6 text-sm">
                    <li>
                        <strong>The Big Limit:</strong> You can contribute up to 20%
                        of your net operational income, capped at ~CHF 36,288 (2025/26
                        figures).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Flexibility:</strong> In good years, max it out to
                        destroy your tax bill. In bad years, scale back.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Diversification:</strong> Since your "human capital"
                        is risky (your business), ensure your 3a investments are diversified
                        globally to offset your local business risk.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
